## Deployment

The demo is now deployed live at: **https://renocomputerfix-demo.up.railway.app**

## What This Demo Proves

1. **Live Data Sync**: Uses Serper API to pull real eBay listings, filtered for laptops only
2. **Automatic Markup**: Applies 30% markup to vendor prices automatically  
3. **Professional Storefront**: Clean, Squarespace-style design with RenoComputerFix branding
4. **Fallback System**: Includes 12 realistic laptop listings if live scraping fails
5. **Production-Ready Feel**: Shows timestamps, sync status, and realistic product grid

## Key Talking Points for Monday's Demo

- **"This is live data"** - Point to the sync timestamp showing it just pulled fresh inventory
- **"30% margin on every laptop"** - Show price comparison (original vs marked up)
- **"Zero manual work"** - Explain the pipeline runs automatically daily/weekly
- **"Extended inventory instantly"** - Customer sees 12+ laptops they couldn't sell before
- **"Squarespace integration ready"** - In production, this writes directly to their actual store

The demo focuses on the core wow moment: Justin seeing his website automatically populated with profitable laptop inventory he never had to source or photograph himself.
